<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB DOOR COMPONENTS DISASSEMBLY AND REASSEMBLY - CHANNELS AND SEALS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1600616" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CHANNELS AND SEALS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The door glass channel seal (weather stripping) is molded for a compression fit in window frame and
                front run channel. No clips are required to retain it. Inner and outer seals in window sill are of a
                similar type.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cab door glass as covered previously under
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_29.xml" xrefid="hl1600615">Door Glass
                        <xref refid="hl1600615"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove button plug from inner upper door panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting bolt under button plug. Also remove screw retaining channel end to lower
                    section of door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove window seal from full length of channel and lift channel from door (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600639">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600639" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600639" filename="../figg16/G1600639.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 39. Removing Glass Front Run Channel</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Front run channel can be removed without removing inner upper panel. Panel has been
                            removed in
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600639">Figure 39</hotlnk>for instructional purposes.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door glass seals (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600640">Figure 40</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600640" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600640" filename="../figg16/G1600640.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 40. Removing Door Glass Channel and Seal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PLUG BUTTON</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SEAL</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Obtain replacement seals as required and insert in door channels.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align front run channel with bottom of vent window and with bracket in bottom of door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure top and bottom of channel with mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place window seal in front run channel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install cab door glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_29.xml" xrefid="hl1600615">DOOR GLASS
                        <xref refid="hl1600615"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
